<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: 'radial-gradient' value with 'em' units</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="https://drafts.csswg.org/css3-images/#gradients" />
        <meta name="flags" content="" />
        <meta name="assert" content="Using 'em unit' values for 'radial-gradient' is supported." />
        <style type="text/css">
            #test
            {
                font-family: Ahem;
                font-size: 30pt;
                border: 1px solid black;
                background-image: radial-gradient(center 2.0em, blue, transparent 0.5em);
                display: inline-block;
                height: 4em;
                width: 1em;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Test passes if there is a blue ellipse in the black box such that the ellipse is the height of the black box without overflowing the box.</p>
        <div id="test"></div>
    </body>
</html>
